land, the author proposes a re-conceptualisation of Northern Irish culture along lines that steer clear of binary oppositions. From the Contents: 'Webs of Significance'; Dis-membering the Past; Divided by Common Cosmologies; A Discourse in Difference; The Process if 'Cruthinitude'; Un Unclaimed Tradition; Ethnic Nationality; The 'Fuzzy Frontier'; The 'Common Ground'  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aCulture conflictxNorthern Ireland. 0aCulture conflictzNorthern Ireland. 0aEthnic groupsxNorthern Ireland. 0aEthnic groupszNorthern Ireland. 0aGroup identityxNorthern Ireland. 0aGroup identityzNorthern Ireland. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aCraith, Máiréad Nic, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782381662?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782381662423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782381662/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK